5. What did you need to do to install the language?
  I opened Visual Studio, choose the fourth icon on the left menu, search PHP, and install "PHP Intelephense".

6. Does this language come with a recommended programming environment? What is it? If not, how did you pick the one that you'll be using?
  The best IDEs in 2021 for PHP Programming comprise of PHPStorm, Zend Studio, Sublime Text, PHP Designer.[4]

7. How do you run programs in that language?
  First create a .php file, enter the code and save it, run the php file by opening a new tab in the browser.[5]

8. How do you write comments in your language?
    1)single line comments: //
    2)muti-line comments: /*  */
    [6]
                    

